                                                                                                               Uco Bank offers discount 
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                          S.K. Goel in Calcutta on Friday. A Telegraph picture                                  
	Calcutta, March 6: Uco Bank today announced a special discount of 0.50 percentage points in interest rates on new home, auto and consumer durables loans.         
	The offer is valid till June 30 this year. A borrower who signs up for a new loan on or before June 30 will get a discount of 50 basis points on our existing rates and can enjoy the waiver throughout the tenure of the loan, Uco Bank chairman and managing director S.K. Goel said.         
	The bank has also reduced its benchmark prime lending rate by 50 basis points to 12.5 per cent with effect from March 1, 2009.         
	According to Goel, The EMIs will be calculated on the basis of the current card rates. However, the accrued benefits will be adjusted at the time of the closure of the loan.                                                                                                                                                               
